  name: Share of landowners who are female - FAO (2017)
  description: >-
    Share of agricultural landowners who are female (%).


    I thought the data came from the FAOSTAT WCAD dataset. But from what I've read [here](https://www.fao.org/3/i4862e/i4862e.pdf), WCAD informs about land management and not landownership. So we can't update this dataset with FAOSTAT data. I think the data comes from [this page](https://www.fao.org/gender-landrights-database/data-map/statistics/en/), where they claim "The data is shown in the interactive map and are also available in graph and table formats." but I haven't found any way to access the data but to copy or scrape the page. In any case the data has not changed. Last time I checked (2023-04-11) the data doesn't seem to have changed with respect to this dataset, so there's no need to update it.
